ALTERNATIVE COMMANDS TO DISPLAY BRANCHES:
================================================================================

Command 1: Show all branches (local and remote)
   $ git branch -a

Command 2: Show only local branches
   $ git branch

Command 3: Show only remote branches
   $ git branch -r

Command 4: Show branches with more detailed information
   $ git branch -vv

Command 5: Show branches with last commit info
   $ git branch -v

================================================================================
DETAILED EXPLANATION OF OUTPUT:
================================================================================

* main
   - The asterisk (*) indicates this is the currently checked out branch
   - "main" is your primary/default branch

bug-fix-typo
   - A local branch (no asterisk, so it's not currently checked out)
   - This is the feature branch you created earlier

remotes/origin/HEAD -> origin/main
   - Points to the default branch on the remote repository
   - Shows that the remote default is the main branch

remotes/origin/bug-fix-typo
   - Remote tracking branch for bug-fix-typo
   - Shows that bug-fix-typo branch exists on the remote (GitHub)

remotes/origin/main
   - Remote tracking branch for main
   - Shows that main branch exists on the remote (GitHub)

