Line 2:   bug-fix-typo
   - Local branch name: bug-fix-typo
   - Space before it means it's not the current branch
   - This branch was created earlier with: git checkout -b bug-fix-typo

Line 3:   remotes/origin/HEAD -> origin/main
   - Remote pointer to the default branch
   - Points to origin/main on the GitHub repository
   - Indicates GitHub's default branch is "main"

Line 4:   remotes/origin/bug-fix-typo
   - Remote tracking branch
   - Tracks the bug-fix-typo branch on GitHub (origin)
   - Shows that your pushed branch exists on remote

Line 5:   remotes/origin/main
   - Remote tracking branch
   - Tracks the main branch on GitHub (origin)
   - Shows that main branch exists on remote

