USEFUL ADDITIONAL COMMANDS:
================================================================================

See branches sorted by last commit date:
$ git branch -a --sort=-committerdate

See branches with status relative to upstream:
$ git branch -a --verbose --verbose

See branches in a graphical tree format:
$ git log --graph --oneline --all --decorate

Show which branches have been merged:
$ git branch --merged

Show which branches have not been merged:
$ git branch --no-merged

Show branches and their remote tracking status:
$ git for-each-ref --format='%(refname:short) <- %(upstream:short)' refs/heads

