   - You're not in a Git repository directory
   - Navigate to your cloned repository folder
   - Run: cd mcino-Introduction-to-Git-and-GitHub

If remote branches don't show:
   - Fetch from remote: git fetch origin
   - Then run: git branch -a

If you see many branches:
   - This is normal if the original repo has multiple branches
   - Look for: main and bug-fix-typo

